!!!
%html
  %head
    %title Unofficial Event Log File Browser for Salesforce
    = stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all'
    = javascript_include_tag 'application'
    = csrf_meta_tags
    = render 'layouts/google_analytics'
  %body
    .navbar.navbar-inverse.navbar-static-top{ style: 'background-color: black;' }
      .container
        .navbar-header
          %button.navbar-toggle{"data-target" => ".navbar-collapse", "data-toggle" => "collapse", type: "button"}
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
            %span.icon-bar
          = link_to(root_path, class: "navbar-brand") do
            %span
            Event Log File Browser for Salesforce
        .collapse.navbar-collapse
          - if logged_in?
            .nav.navbar-nav.navbar-right
              %li.dropdown
                %a{"data-toggle" => "dropdown", href: "#"}
                  = username
                  %b.caret
                %ul.dropdown-menu
                  %li
                    = link_to(logout_path) do
                      %span.glyphicon.glyphicon-log-out
                      %span Logout
        .h4{ style: 'color: red;font-weight: bold;' }
          ANNOUNCEMENT: This app will end-of-life after Summer â€™24 (earliest July 2024). 
          .br
          Please migrate to the new 'Event Log File Browser' in Salesforce, or host this app yourself.
        .link
          = link_to("New Event Log File Browser (by Salesforce)", "https://help.salesforce.com/s/articleView?id=release-notes.rn_security_em_elf_browser.htm")
        .div{ style: 'height: 10px;'}

    .container
      = yield

    #footer
      .container
        %hr
        .div
          = render 'layouts/github_buttons'
        .div
          = link_to("Source Code","https://github.com/tristenmiller/salesforce-elf-browser")
          |
          = link_to("Report Issues", "https://github.com/tristenmiller/salesforce-elf-browser/issues")
          |
          Provided under
          = link_to("MIT license.", "https://github.com/tristenmiller/salesforce-elf-browser/blob/master/MIT-LICENSE")
          Copyright (c) 2023 Salesforce ELF Browser contributors. 

          Safe harbor: the Salesforce ELF browser is not an official Salesforce product we make no guarantees on the safety, security, or maintenance of the project or the deployed app and customers should not base their purchasing decision on the current feature set or future roadmap of this application.
